TENNENT'S Lager has announced 16 of Scotland's freshest unsigned acts that will play the famous T Break stage this summer at T In The Park's new home.A call for demos was put out in March with over a thousand of Scottish unsigned acts responding.Some of the acts include; AmatrArt, Apache Darling, Catholic Action and Be CharlotteTennent's Lager have been supporting Scotland's grassroots music scene through T Break for 20 years, providing unsigned talent a chance to showcase their material to fans, musicians and music industry insiders.the T Break Stage has seen a huge wealth of talent coming through the ranks, with bands such as Biffy Clyro, Snow Patrol, Twin Atlantic and The View all playing the legendary stage.